Here's the full solution:

### XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1"
                           Text="{Binding Name}"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

### ViewModel

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? selectedItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
        {
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        });
        IsRefreshing = false; // stops the spinner
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", SelectedItem);
        SelectedItem = null; // reset so they can re-select
    }
}
```

### Key bindings explained

| Property | Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` (TwoWay) | Shows/hides spinner; set `false` when done |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Fires on pull-down → calls your API |
| `SelectionMode` | `Single` | Enables single-item tap selection |
| `SelectedItem` | `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | Tracks which item is tapped |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on tap → navigates to detail |

### Important notes

- Use **`ObservableCollection<T>`**, not `List<T>`, so the UI updates on add/remove.
- Set `IsRefreshing = false` at the end of your refresh to dismiss the spinner.
- Reset `SelectedItem = null` after navigation so the same item can be re-selected.
- Always set `x:DataType` on the `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- **Never use `ViewCell`** — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, or any `View` as the template root.
